headline: Is Nasdaq (NDAQ) Quietly Transforming From Exchange Operator To Fintech Platform Powerhouse?
summary: Nasdaq, Inc. recently reported its fourth-quarter and full-year 2025 results, showing higher revenue and net income year over year, while its board affirmed a regular quarterly dividend of US$0.27 per share payable on March 30, 2026 to shareholders of record on March 16, 2026. Alongside a completed multiyear share repurchase program and growing use of its Eqlipse technology platform through partners like Japan Exchange Group and Amazon Web Services, Nasdaq’s results highlight its push beyond...

headline: Are Wall Street Analysts Predicting Nasdaq Stock Will Climb or Sink?
summary: Nasdaq has lagged the S&P 500 Index over the past year, yet analysts remain cautiously optimistic, reflecting confidence in the company’s long-term growth potential.

headline: Nasdaq Leans Into Fintech Model With AWS, Eqlipse And IPO Fast Entry
summary: Nasdaq (NasdaqGS:NDAQ) is expanding its fintech capabilities through a cloud partnership with Amazon Web Services and plans to introduce 23/5 trading hours. Japan Exchange Group's Osaka Exchange is adopting Nasdaq's Eqlipse technology for its derivatives platform. Nasdaq has proposed a "fast entry" rule to bring large IPOs into its key indexes more quickly after listing. Nasdaq sits at the center of global equity trading, and these moves signal a broad refresh of how its platforms operate...
